<p>1.CNN models performed much better than ANN models because convolutional layers are better at learning image features such as edges, shapes, and patterns.</p>
<p>2.Adding more layers to the ANN slightly improved its accuracy, but it still could not match the performance of CNNs.</p>
<p>3.Data augmentation improved the CNN's ability to generalize by exposing it to more varied training images, which helped reduce overfitting.
Early stopping prevented unnecessary training by stopping the model when validation loss stopped improving and restoring the best-performing weights.</p>
<p>4.Overall, the CNN with data augmentation achieved the best performance, showing that combining a CNN architecture with augmentation is effective for image classification tasks.</p></span></div>
